Package io.cyborgcode.roa.ui.service.tables

Interface TableElement<K extends Enum<K>>

public interface TableElement<K extends Enum<K>>
Represents a table element that can be interacted with in the UI.

This interface provides methods for retrieving table metadata, such as its type, row representation class, and lifecycle hooks (before and after actions).

Implementations of this interface are used to define specific tables and their associated behaviors within the test automation framework.

      default <T extends io.cyborgcode.roa.ui.components.table.base.TableComponentType> T tableType()

      By default, this method returns DefaultTableTypes.DEFAULT. Implementations may override this method to provide a custom table type.

    • before

      default Consumer<io.cyborgcode.roa.ui.selenium.smart.SmartWebDriver> before()
      Provides a before-action hook that is executed before interacting with the table.

      This method allows implementations to define preconditions, such as waiting for the table to load.

      Returns:
      A Consumer accepting SmartWebDriver for executing preconditions.

    • after

      default Consumer<io.cyborgcode.roa.ui.selenium.smart.SmartWebDriver> after()
      Provides an after-action hook that is executed after interacting with the table.

      This method allows implementations to define post-interaction actions, such as logging interactions or refreshing the UI state.

      Returns:
      A Consumer accepting SmartWebDriver for executing postconditions.
